province_list = [i[2:5] if "内蒙古" in i or "黑龙江" in i else i[2:4] for i in login_place_list]

city_list = [i[5:] if "内蒙古" in i or "黑龙江" in i else i[2:4] if i[2:4] in ["北京", "上海", "天津", "重庆"] 
            else i[4:] for i in login_place_list]

login_cleaned["province"] = province_list
login_cleaned["city"] = city_list
Show code cell source Hide code cell source 
def workday(date):
    """
    - workday Y
    - the other N
    """
    if calendar.is_holiday(date):
        return "N"
    if date.weekday() >= 5:
        if calendar.is_in_lieu(date):
            return "Y"
        return "N"
    return "Y"

user_id_list =  user_cleaned["user_id"].tolist()
recently_logged_list = user_cleaned["recently_logged"].tolist()
userID_recentlyLogged_dict = dict(zip(user_id_list,recently_logged_list))

user_max_login_time = login_cleaned.groupby("user_id")["login_time"].max().to_dict()
userId_login_list = list(user_max_login_time.keys())

for k, v in userID_recentlyLogged_dict.items():
    if v == "--" :
        # and k in  userId_login_list
        v_tmp = user_max_login_time.get(k, "--")
        userID_recentlyLogged_dict[k] = v_tmp
        
user_cleaned["recently_logged"] = user_cleaned["user_id"].map(userID_recentlyLogged_dict)

# Standardize the format of the recently_logged field
format_recently_logged_list = []
for i in user_cleaned["recently_logged"].tolist():
    if len(i) < 19:
        tmp = i.replace("/", "-")
        if tmp.count(":") == 1:
            tmp += ":00"
    else:
        tmp = i.replace("/", "-")
    format_recently_logged_list.append(tmp)
user_cleaned["recently_logged"] = format_recently_logged_list

Heat Map of Login Times by Cities#

Show code cell source Hide code cell source 
city_name, city_data = zip(*login_cleaned[login_cleaned["country"] == "中国"]["city"].value_counts().items())
city_name, city_data = list(city_name), list(city_data)
Show code cell source Hide code cell source 
def city_names(city_list):

    df = cpca.transform(city_list)
    completed = []
    
    unnormal_keywords = ["自治州", "地区", "盟", "林区", "自治县", "特别行政区", "藏族自治州", "蒙古自治州"]
    
    for i in range(len(city_list)):
        raw = city_list[i]  
        province = df.iloc[i]['省']
        city = df.iloc[i]['市']

        if city in  ["省直辖县级行政区划", "自治区直辖县级行政区划"]:
            if not raw.endswith('市'):
                completed.append(f"{raw}市")
            else:
                completed.append(raw)
            continue
        
        if province in ["北京市", "天津市", "上海市", "重庆市"]:
            completed.append(province)

        elif province == "台湾省":
            if city:
                completed.append(f"台湾省{city}")
            else:
                completed.append(f"台湾省{raw}")
        
        elif province in ["香港特别行政区", "澳门特别行政区"]:
            completed.append(province)
            
        elif any(kw in raw for kw in unnormal_keywords):
            completed.append(raw)
        elif city:
            if not city.endswith("市"):
                completed.append(f"{city}市")
            else:
                completed.append(city)
        else:
            completed.append(raw)
    
    return completed

User Login Behavior Analysis Report#

#

  1. Global Activity Difference Analysis

Through geographical heat map analysis, significant differences in activity levels between domestic and overseas users were observed (based on login frequency statistics). The distribution differences may be influenced by the following factors:

Educational policy orientation: Domestic educational informatization policies promote the popularization of online learning platforms.

Technical infrastructure: Higher internet coverage in China supports large-scale online access.

Cultural acceptance: Domestic users have relatively higher acceptance of online education. 2. Domestic Regional Distribution Characteristics

The geographical distribution of login data shows obvious regional aggregation (based on heat map visualization analysis):

Core findings: Eastern coastal agglomeration effect:

  Economically developed provinces such as Guangdong, Zhejiang, and Jiangsu have the highest login frequencies, forming a continuous banded region of high activity.

Prominence of regional centers:

  As the only municipality directly under the central government in western China, Chongqing has significantly higher login volumes than surrounding provinces, reflecting the radiation effect of regional central cities.

Gradient distribution characteristics: Login volumes show a decreasing trend from east to west by geographical location:

  Coastal economic belt --> central region --> southwestern region --> underdeveloped western region. 3. Data Anomalies

Abnormal phenomena:

 Multiple regional logins with the same user_id.

 Missing location information.

Potential cause analysis:

 Possibility of course brushing by proxies.

 Abnormal login patterns may reflect account sharing or automated script usage.

 Further verification is required by combining login time-frequency distribution.

Data collection defects:

 IP location drift (especially for mobile network users).

 Geographical misjudgment caused by VPN usage.

 Unprocessed proxy server access records. 4. Recommendations and Optimization Directions

Establish a user behavior baseline model.

 Define the geographical scope of normal logins.

 Set time-space rationality verification rules.

Enhance data collection quality.

Recommend Courses for Top 5 Users in Learning Progress#

Show code cell source Hide code cell source 
recommendations = {}

for user in tqdm(top5_users, desc="Generate Recommendations"):

    selected_courses = set(study_info_cleaned[study_info_cleaned["user_id"] == user]["course_id"])

    candidate_scores = {}
    for course in selected_courses:
        similar_courses = course_sim_df[course].sort_values(ascending=False)
        for similar_course, score in similar_courses.items():
            if similar_course not in selected_courses:
                candidate_scores[similar_course] = candidate_scores.get(similar_course, 0) + score

    if candidate_scores:
        top_candidates = sorted(candidate_scores.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)[:3]
        recommendations[user] = [course for course, _ in top_candidates]
    else:
        popular_courses = study_info_cleaned["course_id"].value_counts().index[:3].tolist()
        recommendations[user] = popular_courses

print("Recommend Courses for Top 5 Users in Learning Progress：")
for user, courses in recommendations.items():
    print(f"\n user_id {user} Recommend Courses:")
    for i, course in enumerate(courses, 1):
        course_name = f"course_id{course}"
        print(f"{i}. {course_name}")
